{
  "database": {
    "technology": "PostgreSQL 15",
    "models": [
      {
        "name": "User",
        "fields": {
          "id": "Integer (Primary Key)",
          "email": "String (Unique, 255 chars)",
          "hashed_password": "String (255 chars)",
          "full_name": "String (100 chars, nullable)",
          "created_at": "DateTime (default now)"
        },
        "relations": [
          "One-to-Many avec Task"
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "Task",
        "fields": {
          "id": "Integer (Primary Key)",
          "title": "String (100 chars)",
          "description": "Text (nullable)",
          "status": "Enum('todo', 'in_progress', 'done')",
          "priority": "Enum('low', 'medium', 'high')",
          "due_date": "Date (nullable)",
          "created_at": "DateTime (default now)",
          "updated_at": "DateTime (default now, on update)",
          "user_id": "Integer (Foreign Key)"
        },
        "relations": [
          "Many-to-One avec User"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "indexes": [
      "CREATE INDEX idx_task_user_id ON task(user_id)",
      "CREATE INDEX idx_task_status ON task(status)",
      "CREATE INDEX idx_task_priority ON task(priority)"
    ],
    "instructions": "Oumeyma, utilise SQLAlchemy avec Alembic pour les migrations. Cr\u00e9e les mod\u00e8les User et Task avec les champs sp\u00e9cifi\u00e9s. Impl\u00e9mente les relations One-to-Many entre User et Task. Ajoute les indexes pour optimiser les requ\u00eates de filtrage. Configure la base de donn\u00e9es avec un utilisateur d\u00e9di\u00e9 et un sch\u00e9ma 'todo_app'."
  },
  "backend": {
    "technology": "FastAPI (Python 3.10)",
    "endpoints": [
      {
        "path": "/auth/register",
        "method": "POST",
        "description": "Inscription utilisateur",
        "auth_required": false,
        "request_body": {
          "email": "string",
          "password": "string",
          "full_name": "string (optional)"
        },
        "response": {
          "access_token": "string",
          "token_type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/auth/login",
        "method": "POST",
        "description": "Connexion utilisateur",
        "auth_required": false,
        "request_body": {
          "username": "string (email)",
          "password": "string"
        },
        "response": {
          "access_token": "string",
          "token_type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/tasks",
        "method": "GET",
        "description": "Liste des t\u00e2ches avec filtres",
        "auth_required": true,
        "query_params": {
          "status": "string (optional, enum: todo,in_progress,done)",
          "priority": "string (optional, enum: low,medium,high)",
          "limit": "integer (optional, default: 10)",
          "offset": "integer (optional, default: 0)"
        },
        "response": {
          "tasks": [
            {
              "id": "integer",
              "title": "string",
              "status": "string",
              "priority": "string",
              "due_date": "string (date)"
            }
          ],
          "total": "integer"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/tasks",
        "method": "POST",
        "description": "Cr\u00e9er une t\u00e2che",
        "auth_required": true,
        "request_body": {
          "title": "string",
          "description": "string (optional)",
          "status": "string (optional, default: todo)",
          "priority": "string (optional, default: medium)",
          "due_date": "string (date, optional)"
        },
        "response": {
          "id": "integer",
          "title": "string",
          "status": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/tasks/{task_id}",
        "method": "GET",
        "description": "R\u00e9cup\u00e9rer une t\u00e2che",
        "auth_required": true,
        "response": {
          "id": "integer",
          "title": "string",
          "description": "string",
          "status": "string",
          "priority": "string",
          "due_date": "string (date)",
          "created_at": "string (datetime)",
          "updated_at": "string (datetime)"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/tasks/{task_id}",
        "method": "PUT",
        "description": "Mettre \u00e0 jour une t\u00e2che",
        "auth_required": true,
        "request_body": {
          "title": "string (optional)",
          "description": "string (optional)",
          "status": "string (optional)",
          "priority": "string (optional)",
          "due_date": "string (date, optional)"
        },
        "response": {
          "id": "integer",
          "title": "string",
          "status": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/tasks/{task_id}",
        "method": "DELETE",
        "description": "Supprimer une t\u00e2che",
        "auth_required": true,
        "response": {
          "detail": "string"
        }
      }
    ],
    "auth": {
      "approach": "JWT avec python-jose (jose) et passlib (bcrypt)",
      "token_expiration": "30 minutes",
      "algorithm": "HS256",
      "secret_key": "\u00c0 g\u00e9n\u00e9rer via openssl rand -hex 32"
    },
    "structure": {
      "routers": [
        "auth.py (routes /auth)",
        "tasks.py (routes /tasks)"
      ],
      "services": [
        "users.py (logique m\u00e9tier utilisateurs)",
        "tasks.py (logique m\u00e9tier t\u00e2ches)"
      ],
      "models": [
        "user.py (mod\u00e8le User)",
        "task.py (mod\u00e8le Task)"
      ],
      "utils": [
        "jwt.py (utilitaires JWT)",
        "security.py (hashage des mots de passe)"
      ],
      "config": "config.py (variables d'environnement avec Pydantic)"
    },
    "instructions": "Akram, impl\u00e9mente les endpoints list\u00e9s avec FastAPI. Utilise SQLAlchemy pour les interactions avec la base de donn\u00e9es. Impl\u00e9mente l'authentification JWT avec les sp\u00e9cifications fournies. Structure le code selon les modules indiqu\u00e9s. Ajoute des tests unitaires pour chaque endpoint avec pytest. Configure les CORS pour permettre les requ\u00eates depuis le frontend. Utilise Pydantic pour la validation des donn\u00e9es."
  },
  "frontend": {
    "technology": "React 18 + TypeScript + Vite",
    "pages": [
      {
        "name": "LoginPage",
        "path": "/login",
        "components": [
          "LoginForm",
          "AuthLayout"
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "RegisterPage",
        "path": "/register",
        "components": [
          "RegisterForm",
          "AuthLayout"
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "DashboardPage",
        "path": "/",
        "components": [
          "TaskList",
          "TaskFilters",
          "TaskForm",
          "DashboardLayout",
          "ProtectedRoute"
        ]
      },
      {
        "name": "NotFoundPage",
        "path": "*",
        "components": [
          "NotFound"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "components": [
      {
        "name": "TaskList",
        "description": "Affiche la liste des t\u00e2ches avec pagination. Permet de filtrer par statut et priorit\u00e9.",
        "props": {
          "tasks": "Task[]",
          "onTaskUpdate": "function",
          "onTaskDelete": "function"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "TaskFilters",
        "description": "Composant de filtres pour le statut et la priorit\u00e9 des t\u00e2ches.",
        "props": {
          "onFilterChange": "function"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "TaskForm",
        "description": "Formulaire pour cr\u00e9er ou modifier une t\u00e2che.",
        "props": {
          "task": "Task (optional)",
          "onSubmit": "function"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "AuthLayout",
        "description": "Layout pour les pages d'authentification."
      },
      {
        "name": "DashboardLayout",
        "description": "Layout pour le tableau de bord avec header et sidebar."
      },
      {
        "name": "ProtectedRoute",
        "description": "Composant pour prot\u00e9ger les routes n\u00e9cessitant une authentification."
      }
    ],
    "state_management": {
      "approach": "React Context + useReducer",
      "contexts": [
        "AuthContext (gestion de l'\u00e9tat d'authentification)",
        "TaskContext (gestion de l'\u00e9tat des t\u00e2ches)"
      ]
    },
    "styling": {
      "library": "Tailwind CSS",
      "approach": "Utility-first avec classes personnalis\u00e9es"
    },
    "routing": {
      "library": "React Router v6",
      "routes": [
        {
          "path": "/login",
          "element": "<LoginPage />"
        },
        {
          "path": "/register",
          "element": "<RegisterPage />"
        },
        {
          "path": "/",
          "element": "<ProtectedRoute><DashboardPage /></ProtectedRoute>"
        },
        {
          "path": "*",
          "element": "<NotFoundPage />"
        }
      ]
    },
    "api_client": {
      "library": "Axios",
      "base_url": "http://localhost:8000",
      "interceptors": [
        "Ajout du token JWT dans les headers pour les requ\u00eates authentifi\u00e9es",
        "Gestion des erreurs 401 (d\u00e9connexion automatique)"
      ]
    },
    "instructions": "Mactar, cr\u00e9e les pages et composants list\u00e9s avec TypeScript. Impl\u00e9mente le routing avec React Router. Utilise Tailwind CSS pour le styling. Cr\u00e9e les contextes AuthContext et TaskContext pour la gestion de l'\u00e9tat. Impl\u00e9mente le ProtectedRoute pour prot\u00e9ger les routes n\u00e9cessitant une authentification. Utilise Axios pour les appels API avec les interceptors sp\u00e9cifi\u00e9s. Ajoute des tests unitaires avec Jest et React Testing Library. Impl\u00e9mente les formulaires avec React Hook Form pour une meilleure gestion des validations."
  },
  "auth": "JWT avec python-jose (backend) et stockage dans le localStorage (frontend)",
  "cache": "none",
  "message_broker": "none",
  "container": {
    "docker": {
      "files": [
        "Dockerfile pour le backend (FastAPI)",
        "Dockerfile pour le frontend (Nginx)",
        "docker-compose.yml pour orchestrer backend, frontend et base de donn\u00e9es"
      ],
      "instructions": "Cr\u00e9e un Dockerfile multi-stage pour le backend avec Python 3.10. Utilise un Dockerfile pour le frontend avec Nginx pour servir les fichiers statiques. Configure docker-compose.yml pour lancer les services backend, frontend et PostgreSQL avec les variables d'environnement n\u00e9cessaires. Ajoute un service pour pgAdmin pour la gestion de la base de donn\u00e9es en d\u00e9veloppement."
    }
  },
  "cloud": "D\u00e9ploiement local pour le d\u00e9veloppement. CI/CD configur\u00e9 pour d\u00e9ployer sur un service comme Render ou Railway en production."
}